  "texts": [
    "This complexity arises because multiple hyperspectral images can be derived from the same RGB image, a phenomenon known as metamerism.",
    "Consequently, this can lead to inaccuracies in the reconstructed hyperspectral images, stemming from both the fundamental limitations of RGB images and the complexities involved in solving this type of inverse problem.",
    "Ongoing research and advancements in image reconstruction and sensor technology are essential for overcoming the challenges of HSI reconstruction.",
    "Currently, computational limitations restrict its applications, but the development of interactive software could broaden its use across various fields (Ahmed et al. 2024e).",
    "Additionally, integrating compressed spectral imaging (Wang et al. 2015) into the RGB-to-HSI reconstruction process can offer a promising solution to enhance reconstruction efficiency."
  ],
